Rewrite the regex named group using the old formPHP 5.2.2 introduced named groups defined as (?<name>...) or (?'name'...) likenwhat it is used in the AsseticFilterBaseCssFilter. Through my research, Infound that this was enabled by the version 7 of PCRE (seenhttp://www.pcre.org/changelog.txt version 7.0 line 34). You can see what PCREnversion is used in each version of PHP here :nhttp://www.php.net/manual/fr/pcre.installation.phpnnFor a reason I do not fully understand, PHP in CentOS 5.8 was compiled withnversion 6.6 of PCRE that do not support that new way of defining named groups.nYou can know which version of PCRE PHP is using  by executing that line :nnphp -r 'echo PCRE_VERSION;'nnSo to fix that problem, I modified the code to use the old way of definingnnamed group, using the uppercase P.n

bug #723 ScssphpFilter - do not add empty load path as import path (aaukt)This PR was merged into the 1.3-dev branch.nnDiscussionn----------nnScssphpFilter - do not add empty load path as import pathnnThis has in part to do with #164 and in part with leafo/scssphp#237.nnWhen you iterate in https://github.com/kriswallsmith/assetic/blob/master/src/Assetic/Factory/AssetFactory.php#L254 over a AssetReference that references a AssetCollection the call to getSourceDirectory() in https://github.com/kriswallsmith/assetic/blob/master/src/Assetic/Factory/AssetFactory.php#L277 would return nothing (null).nnThe ScssphpFilter would then call addImportPath() on the scss compiler with null which results in an exception call_user_func() expects parameter 1 to be a valid callback, no array or string given, which would in turn keep imports from being parsed and replaced properlynnCommitsn-------nnae950df ScssphpFilter - do not add empty load path as import pathn
